div1.p: In the District Court holding Terms at Seattle WT before the Hon Roger S Greene Judge thereof at Chambers
In the matter of the applicant of Ah Korn Ah Min and Ah Sin for writ of Habeas Corpus
The Territory of Washington County of King

1 To the Hon Roger S Greene Judge of the above named Court your petitioner Ah Korn Ah Min and Ah Sin come now and respectively represent that they are restrained of their liberty by James H Woolery Cheif of Police in the City of Seattle in the Territory of Washington.

2 That the Court of their said restrained according to the best of their knowledge and belief is a true and conviction under the respective Complaints hereto attached of against each of them respectively had before S B Vrooman City Justice of the Peace from said City of Seattle as appear upon said complaints
that said section I of Division 2 of Ordinance No 551 of said City of Seattle is void and of no affect in the that the same is in conflict with the general laws of the Territory of Washington and for the that the city Common Counsel of City had no power or authority to enact the in manner and from or the were appears.

3rd that they each make this application for themself respectively in their own person and also that the writ of Habeas Corpus issue and that they be discharged from their custody in the reason that their will restraint is illegal.
J J Hurnes Atty for Applicants
The Territory of Washington County of King

Ah Korn Ah Sin and Ah Min being first duly sworn each for himself on his oath says that they are the applicants herin that they have heard the foregoing
petition and that they know the contents therof and that the same is true as they believe
Witness E A Gardner () () () A Ah Korn Ah Min Ah Lin
Signed in my presence and sworn before me this 11th day of Sept 1884
T J Hurnes Notary Public for King Co W.T.
